12.23	Celibate	Celibacy	Celibacy is a personal commitment to avoiding sexual relations, in particular a vow from marriage. Typically celibacy involves avoiding all romantic relationships of any kind. An individual may choose celibacy for religious reasons, such as is the case for priests in some religions, for reasons of personal development and self-discovery, or for many other reasons. Historically many cultures have venerated celibacy in certain individuals seeing the commitment as a form of discipline to be admired.	
